 Two things I can add. Clean your LINE. Really. Wipe the dirt off of it. coat it with Glide or SA line cleaner.<br>
  I do remember us working on your back cast.<br>
 Try this; Lay a rope out behind you, Make your back cast, let in lay on the gound behind you. Did it land on the rope?<br>
 Did it fall to one side?. Did it fail to get all the way back?<br>
 This is a way to tell just what is happing behind you.<br>
 I know you can get the forward cast. Often your forward cast is enough to pull the slack left over from a slightly off back cast. When you get to the long cast you have to get ALL the slack out on the back cast.<br>
